e</i> investment banks (J.P. Morgan, Evercore, and Guggenheim Securities) a=
nd two high-powered law firms (Kirkland &amp; Ellis and Wachtell Lipton) to=
 aid in the restructuring. =E2=80=9CYou don=E2=80=99t need three M&amp;A ad=
visors and two legal advisors just to reorganize the divisions of your comp=
any,=E2=80=9D Bill wrote. =E2=80=9CInstead, you pay their considerable fees=
 so they can meticulously analyze what a spinoff, sale, or some other strat=
egic separation of the [WBD cable networks] would look like, including when=
 and how to announce it, how much debt to pile on to it, and whether that b=
usiness should try to bring in a private equity partner. And, of course, yo=
u don=E2=80=99t include a detail like this in a press release
unless you want the market to know <i>exactly </i>what you=E2=80=99re doing=
=2E=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>What is the like=
ly outcome? =E2=80=9CIn a couple weeks=
 or months, perhaps, I would not be the least bit surprised to hear that Za=
z is contemplating shoving the [cable networks] off on their own boat, with=
 a large chunk of WBD=E2=80=99s remaining debt and a big investment from a =
private equity or alternative asset management firm,=E2=80=9D Bill wrote. =
=E2=80=9CI suspect the likes of Apollo, Blackstone, KKR <i>et al. </i>have =
already started to dig into this opportunity, anxious to emulate the signif=
icant windfall that TPG received, and continues to enjoy, from its acquisit=
ion of DirecTV from AT&amp;T.=E2=80=9D (Full disclosure: TPG is an investor=
 in Puck.)<br/><br/></li><li><i>Netflix=E2=80=99s Sunday Ticket heist</i>: =
Last week, my ears perked up when I heard that <b>Lori Conkling</b> was mov=
ing from YouTube to Netflix. Conkling, after all, was one of the chief nego=
tiators who brought NFL Sunday Ticket to YouTube TV, and her move
seemed to suggest that Netflix was about to get <i>really</i> serious about=
 investing in sports rights. But, as Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <b>Lucas Shaw</b> =
reported last night, Conkling will oversee all of Netflix=E2=80=99s TV and =
film licensing from U.S. studios and networks=E2=80=94<i>i.e.</i>, her job =
does not appear to be focused on sports.<br/><br/>By the same token, Conkli=
ng=E2=80=99s departure doesn=E2=80=99t necessarily mean that YouTube TV is =
stepping back from sports. Remember, it was just two months ago that YouTub=
e poached <b>Jen Chun </b>from the NBA to become managing director and head=
 of sports and studio partnerships, a position that reported in to Conkling=
, who was global head of TV, film, and sports partnerships.</li></ol></td>
