way he has. He=E2=80=99s been very clear from moment one that he wants to b=
e the highest-paid guy at ESPN, and if not, he=E2=80=99s comfortable leavin=
g.
<br/><br/>Bluffing is tough, especially with ESPN=E2=80=94you have to be pr=
epared for them to call your bluff. And I don=E2=80=99t think <i>anyone </i=
>believes Stephen A. is bluffing, because he doesn=E2=80=99t need to. He=E2=
=80=99s somebody who=E2=80=99s proven that he moves the needle without thos=
e four letters. He has a legitimate fan base and audience, and it=E2=80=99s=
 an audience that will move with him. <br/><br/>For someone who=E2=80=99s a=
s high-profile as he is, he works his ass off. He=E2=80=99s all over the pl=
ace. He works, man. He=E2=80=99s earned every penny. And <i>good for him</i=
>, is what I would say. And good for ESPN, for recognizing a homegrown tale=
nt and rewarding that. From my point of view, I=E2=80=99m sort of like, <i>=
Thank you, Stephen A., because you just reset the market</i>.<br/><br/><b>A=
s you mentioned, Stephen A. is a =E2=80=9Cneedle-mover,=E2=80=9D as they sa=
y in Bristol. And if you talk to Jimmy Pitaro, he has focus groups, ratings=
, and information to show that there=E2=80=99s Stephen A., McAfee, Greeny, =
S.V.P., and maybe
one or two others who <i>actually</i> move the needle.</b><br/><br/>It depe=
nds on how you define =E2=80=9Cneedle-moving.=E2=80=9D ESPN=E2=80=99s <b>Mi=
ke Clay</b> moves the needle. Mike Clay does fantasy and betting, and he do=
es it very well. If you look at who subscribes to ESPN+ on the written side=
, I=E2=80=99d bet Mike Clay is a top-three subscription driver. <b>Bill Bar=
nwell</b> is somebody who moves the needle. I was surprised that <b>Zach Lo=
we</b> got let go, because I think he=E2=80=99s another person who moves th=
e needle. People are willing to pay to read Bill Barnwell; people are willi=
ng to pay to read Zach Lowe; and people are willing to pay to read Mike Cla=
y. I wouldn=E2=80=99t expect you to name those guys as needle-movers, becau=
se they=E2=80=99re not big, bold-faced names like some other talent=E2=80=
=94but again, it depends on how you define moving the needle.<br/><br/><b>F=
or somebody in an on-air role, how can they become a needle-mover? Is that =
something you can work toward?</b><br/><br/>I think you have to
be really, really good at what you do. But it=E2=80=99s not enough to just =
